@asqui is correct and @asafpelegcodes, you need to try your experiments on Python 3.
For what it's worth, I don't think any exception catching is needed here, just line 704.
Any type errors that occur will be bubbled up.

I'd recommend
1) downloading this to country-us.csv.tmp;
2) verifying that the .tmp file is non-zero size;
3) verifying that the .tmp file matches the Github SHA; and then
4) renaming the .tmp file to country-us.csv

This would ensure that we're not overwriting a potentially-good csv.

