The default arguments can be `None`, and in the constructor you can do:

    if arg is None:
        arg = ...

Ok, let me fix it. It's because clang-format tries to align to above line.

Note: some librealsense code has following alignment.
```
static rs_context*                              acquire_instance();
static void                                         release_instance();
static int                                            ref_count;
static std::mutex                               instance_lock;
static rs_context*                             instance;
```

It'll be changed to
```
static rs_context* acquire_instance();
static void release_instance();
static int ref_count;
static std::mutex instance_lock;
static rs_context* instance;
```

You probably want something more like:

```js
ga('set', 'page', '/' + pluginString);
ga('send', 'pageview');
```

See https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/analyticsjs/single-page-applications. Note the "Handling multiple URLs for the same resource" section which basically recommends we remove the hash.
